title: Cheese-topped Tuna Burgers
summary: Cheese-topped Tuna Burgers might be just the main course you are searching for. One portion of this dish contains roughly 16g of protein, 21g of fat, and a total of 357 calories. This recipe serves 8. For $1.09 per serving, this recipe covers 15% of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. 1 person has made this recipe and would make it again. A mixture of mayonnaise, land o deli american cheese, hamburger buns, and a handful of other ingredients are all it takes to make this recipe so scrumptious. To use up the butter you could follow this main course with the Cinnamon Butter Cake as a dessert. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes roughly 20 minutes. It is a good option if you're following a pescatarian diet. It is a reasonably priced recipe for fans of American food. All things considered, we decided this recipe deserves a spoonacular score of 43%. This score is good. Try Cheese-Topped Tuna Casserole, Sauerkraut Topped Brat Burgers, and Easy Cheesy Topped Burgers for similar recipes.

winePairing.pairingText: Tuna works really well with Merlot, Pinot Noir, and rosé Wine. Though fish is often paired with white wine, 'meatier' fish like tuna can absolutely go with red wine. A Rosé will also pair nicely, particularly if your tunan is prepared with ingredients better suited to a white wine. One wine you could try is Raymond R Collection Merlot. It has 4.1 out of 5 stars and a bottle costs about 12 dollars.

productMatches.title: Raymond R Collection Merlot
productMatches.description: The Merlot fills the mouth with smooth cherry, raspberry and plum flavors along with hints of earth and spice in the toasty vanilla finish. Full-bodied, yet approachable, with a good balance of acid and tannins. Pair with anything from grilled salmon, pork tenderloin, barbequed chicken and ribs to Thai red curry or Moroccan tagine.
